Macky established the People's Conservatorium in 1917 in Melbourne and managed it until she emigrated to England in 1932.
After returning to Australia in 1946, she composed numerous works that were regularly performed in Melbourne, and occasionally broadcast on Australian radio.
In 1922, Macky became committed to Anthroposophy as a result of hearing lectures given by Rudolf Steiner at the Oxford Conference.

Macky established, together with the Italian artist Ernesto Genoni, regular Anthroposophy meetings in Melbourne from 1928 and they founded the Michael Group, a branch of the Anthroposophical Society in Melbourne in 1932.

Anne Macky (1887-1964) was an Australian composer, pianist, occultist, student of and coauthor with Aleister Crowley of the influential Crowleian book on Thelema magick, Magick Without Tears Magick Without Tears.
